    "text": [
        "An immensely controversial phenomenon in the contemporary epoch relates to whether the best teaching for a child at the house or school. There is no denying the fact that teaching a child in both places has several effects on children. This essay will elaborate on my visions with illustrations and a rational conclusion in the forthcoming paragraphs.",
        "To commence with, It has been argued by some crowd that teaching a child at home is more pivotal than going their school. This has positive effects on children because parents more focus on their children and they may know specifically about their problems of education. For example, a couple who are educated, interest their children at a house and give them their knowledge more than a teacher at a school. In contrast, juveniles may not be socialized with their peers. This leads them to be social issues in the long run. To cite an example, the latest study, conducted by researchers, reveals that more than half of pupils who are educated by parents and a tutor at the house tend to more suffer social problems compared to their peers going to school, according to Dumlup\u0131nar University.",
        "On the other hand, in terms of self-improvement, the school are play a vital role for children as they may learn a variety of knowledge from the teachers and their counterparts. This is the effective improvement of their growth, as argued by others. Additionally, schools are funded by governments and there are facilities where children can not find opportunities at the house to be socialized.",
        "In conclusion, to recapitulate, the aforementioned arguments, It can not be neglected that educating a child at a house has some beneficial effects. However, children should go to school. This is because It has crucial for them in the long run."
